properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 16 at 7:49PM CST until February 17 at 9:00PM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Slippery Travel Expected Monday...

.Accumulating snow is expected on Monday and Monday evening. This
snow will be mixed with sleet, freezing rain, and rain at times
for areas south of Interstate 90. Total snow accumulation of 2 to
5 inches is expected for much of the area, highest from northeast
Iowa into western and central Wisconsin.

Roads will become snow-covered and hazardous. This includes the
morning commute in northeast Iowa and southeast Minnesota and
the evening commute for the entire area.

* WHAT...Periods of snow. Snow may mix with sleet, freezing rain,
or just rain across southwest Wisconsin during the afternoon.
Total snow accumulations of 2 to 5 inches and ice accumulations
of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Portions of central, southwest and west central
Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 9 PM CST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Hourly snowfall rates are possible on
Monday afternoon.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 9 PM CST MONDAY
